<subSubSection id="6D837C851038FFA7DBB2FD0C48E42F3C" pageId="29" pageNumber="130" type="description">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1038FFA7DBB2FD0C4D58294C" blockId="29.[151,447,546,609]" box="[151,365,583,609]" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1038FFA7DBBAFD0C4CC3294C" box="[159,246,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–28" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1336]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[162,1425,181,1336]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–28. Asianthrips species. (23) A. setifer, female (mac); (24) A. sufflavus, female (mac); (25) A. sulawesiensis, female (mac). A. taiwanus, 26–27; (26) Female (mac); (27) Male (mic); (28) A. vietnamensis, female (mac)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404872/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Figs 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1038FFA7DA27FD0C4D50294C" box="[258,357,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 124–130" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 124–130. Asianthrips setifer, sp. n., female (mac). (124) Head &amp; pronotum; (125) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect; (126) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (127) Basantra–mesopresternum (holotype); (128) Mesopresternum (a paratype); (129) Fore wing; (130) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404920/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">124–129</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1038FFA7DBB2FDC44D7E2870" blockId="29.[151,1437,655,1293]" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1038FFA7DBB2FDC44D412985" box="[151,372,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Colour and structure very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1038FFA7D830FDC44FB02984" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[789,901,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1038FFA7D830FDC44FB02984" box="[789,901,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">A. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1038FFA7D8B6FDC44FD32984" box="[915,998,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–28" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1336]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[162,1425,181,1336]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–28. Asianthrips species. (23) A. setifer, female (mac); (24) A. sufflavus, female (mac); (25) A. sulawesiensis, female (mac). A. taiwanus, 26–27; (26) Female (mac); (27) Male (mic); (28) A. vietnamensis, female (mac)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404872/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
), but distinct in the following character states:Antennal segments IV and V each with a series of 7–11 setae arranged in a longitudinal line on ventral surface (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1038FFA7DB85FD9C4D3429DC" box="[160,257,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 124–130" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 124–130. Asianthrips setifer, sp. n., female (mac). (124) Head &amp; pronotum; (125) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect; (126) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (127) Basantra–mesopresternum (holotype); (128) Mesopresternum (a paratype); (129) Fore wing; (130) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404920/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
); eyes 0.42 times as long as head (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1038FFA7D95EFD9C4EE829DC" box="[635,733,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 124–130" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 124–130. Asianthrips setifer, sp. n., female (mac). (124) Head &amp; pronotum; (125) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect; (126) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (127) Basantra–mesopresternum (holotype); (128) Mesopresternum (a paratype); (129) Fore wing; (130) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404920/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Fig. 124</figureCitation>
); posterior portion of metanotum longitudinally reticulated, but weak; mesopresternum and mesoeusternum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1038FFA7D9B5FDB04F7C2838" box="[656,841,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 124–130" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 124–130. Asianthrips setifer, sp. n., female (mac). (124) Head &amp; pronotum; (125) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect; (126) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (127) Basantra–mesopresternum (holotype); (128) Mesopresternum (a paratype); (129) Fore wing; (130) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404920/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Figs. 127 &amp; 128</figureCitation>
) narrowly fused medially, with long sutures between them at both sides, one of which is longer than 1/3 of the posterior width of mesopresternum; fore wing with 3–5 duplicated cilia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1038FFA7DBE2FC2C48E42F3C" blockId="29.[151,1437,655,1293]" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1038FFA7DBE2FC2C4D4328AC" bold="true" box="[199,374,871,897]" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1038FFA7DAC0FC2C4E7228AC" box="[485,583,871,897]" pageId="29" pageNumber="130">holotype</typeStatus>
(mac.) in microns. Distended body length 1840. Head length 170, width across cheeks 160. Compound eye dorsal length 71–72. Pronotum length 90, width 211. Fore wing length about 720. Tube length 100, width across base 55. Antenna length about 370, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 52 (30), 55 (30), 50 (26), 45 (23), 45 (21), 30 (13). Postocular setae 66–70. Pronotal aa 43–44, am 42–43, ml 52–53, pa 55–56, epim 62–63. S1 setae on tergite IX 70–71, S2 setae on tergite IX 75–75. Anal setae?105.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
